name: microservice
description: containerization, ochestration, service mesh, service discovery, asynchronous communication, monitoring, and other distributed system exploration stuff is right here

name: reservation-system-nest-microservices
description: This project includes a reservation system with payments and email notification. A production grade code implemented in NESTJS microservices.

name: flight-management-system
description: Flight Management System developed using Microservices Architecture with features like CRUD operations, JWT Auth, Authorization, Rate Limiting, Reverse Proxy and CRON jobs.

name: subscribers-notification-system
description: A spring boot microservices application which uses technologies like KAKFA, DOCKER, POSTGRESQL databases. User creates a template and add subscribers for their templates. Also billing service take care of billing and subscription of all users. Owner send notification to all subscribers added to a particular template.

name: pytorch-golang-plant-system
description: This repository contains the source code for a Smart Plant Watering System, an automated solution for monitoring and managing the watering needs of potted plants. The system integrates deep learning, microservices in Golang, and databases to create an intelligent and efficient plant care solution.

name: PostIt
description: An assessment project on a microservices-based social media system utilizing .NET, Angular, RabbitMQ, and MSSQL. The project incorporates three software design principles: Microservices architecture, Domain-Driven Design (DDD), and Command Query Responsibility Segregation (CQRS).

name: circuit-breaker-resilience4j-redis-spring
description: Fault tolerance is a crucial aspect of microservices system design. Here, I implemented the circuit breaker pattern using Resilience4j for services written in Java/Spring Boot, with Redis as a fallback caching mechanism.

name: PFE-Commune_Marrakech
description: This microservice forms part of a larger project focused on Marrakech Municipality's integrated Information System. Its objective is to manage contracts, documents, and investments, elevating operational efficiency by fostering better collaboration with delegates and Local Development Companies (LDCs).
